The evidence with the title 'Paying for college on minimum wage in 1978 was easier ... ' says Aug 8, 2014  ... The student would need to hold down the same minimum - wage job for 14 weeks to net the dough she'd need for a year's worth of tuition. If the minimum wage were as high in real dollars as it was in 1978 , the same worker would need to hold down her gig for 315 hours , or 10.5 work weeks. It's worth noting  ... 
